Description:
Address:
120 Bloor Street East
Job Family Group:
Audit, Risk & Compliance
Quantitative Audit Manager, Capital Markets Audit
Why join BMO as an Audit Manager?
This is an ideal role for quantitative finance professionals who aspire to a career in model risk, without limiting themselves to a specific model area. The role will offer an ideal blend of higher learning and real world practice, exposing you to some of the latest technologies and best practice approaches to internal Audit, and developing risk frameworks. It offers an opportunity to understand the different business areas and models used within a large financial institution, while continuously developing analytical skills and building a knowledge base in quantitative analytics and risk modelling.
Role Description
BMO’s Corporate Audit Department helps protect against the risk of loss and reputational damage, and provides vital assurance to the Board of Directors and senior management as to the quality and effectiveness of the internal control system. The Quantitative Audit Manager will work with a Director or Senior Audit Manager on executing elements of audits across different teams, with a focus on modelling, quantitative analysis, and audit execution activities.
What will a typical day look like?
Every day will be different! An ideal role for someone who loves quantitative modelling, you will be asked to take on a number of activities that will include supporting team members through:
Understanding models used by various businesses;
Presenting these models and any potential weaknesses/findings to other team and bank members, thus assisting senior managers in determining the Bank’s risk strategy;
Ensuring all model documentation is compliant with Corporate policies, standards and guidelines;
Working with the team to evaluate the strength of the business risk framework.
Our expectation is that you’ll come to the job every day with a can-do attitude and a commitment to:
Continually demonstrating a desire to learn new tools and business processes;
Demonstrating your ability to investigate and solve problems creatively and innovatively;
Collaborating effectively with fellow team members and project stakeholders;
Proactively managing individual tasks and work assignments.
Qualifications
At least Masters degree in Quantitative Finance or related areas;
At least 2 years experience with quantitative analysis, research and/or statistical modelling;
Demonstrated analytical ability and aptitude for logical and critical thinking;
Excellent written and communication skills;
Strong attention to detail;
Excellent computer and Excel skills; advanced knowledge of programming languages is useful for some roles.
We’re here to help
At BMO we are driven by a shared Purpose: Boldly Grow the Good in business and life. It calls on us to create lasting, positive change for our customers, our communities and our people. By working together, innovating and pushing boundaries, we transform lives and businesses, and power economic growth around the world.
As a member of the BMO team you are valued, respected and heard, and you have more ways to grow and make an impact. We strive to help you make an impact from day one – for yourself and our customers. We’ll support you with the tools and resources you need to reach new milestones, as you help our customers reach theirs. From in-depth training and coaching, to manager support and network-building opportunities, we’ll help you gain valuable experience, and broaden your skillset.
To find out more visit us at https://bmocareers.com .
BMO is committed to an inclusive, equitable and accessible workplace. By learning from each other’s differences, we gain strength through our people and our perspectives. Accommodations are available on request for candidates taking part in all aspects of the selection process. To request accommodation, please contact your recruiter.

We are currently seeking a Sales Operations Manager to join our Business Operations team in Toronto or Vancouver.
The team
Our BizOps team, led by our Chief Operations Officer, is responsible for providing data insights on all aspects of our business practices. They use data to identify opportunities for process improvement and challenge us to a different thinking level. In 2017, this team was recognized as Team of the Year by BC Tech Association at the Technology Impact Awards.
Who you are:
We're looking for a talented and experienced Sales Operation leader that is passionate about accelerating our sales team with the tools, data, skills and processes they need to do their best work. Reporting to the Senior Director of Revenue Operations and working closely with our SVP of Sales, broader sales leadership team and an array of stakeholders from across the business, you will lead the charge when it comes to business process innovation, systems design, and enablement for our revenue-generating teams (Sales, Marketing and Customer Success).
What you'll be doing
Deeply analysing our data to make recommendations on how to optimize our revenue performance while reducing our cost of sales;
Providing reports, dashboards and other intelligence essential to the sales organization using our BI tool (Looker) and Salesforce.com;
Managing, mentoring and developing Clio's Sales Operations team;
Building trust with stakeholders using curiosity and empathy;
Acting as a dedicated partner to our SVP sales and the broader sales and account management leadership team;
Managing a Sales Operations roadmap and business requirements to enable our strategic plan;
Accelerating our performance and revenue growth by enabling our sales team with insights, planning, forecasting and strategic input on a proactive basis;
Assisting with attainment planning including sales incentive analysis, segmentation strategy and goal-setting;
Ensuring a high level of data quality;
Contributing to a data-driven culture by supporting discussions with data and disseminating best practices;
Providing tactical support to partner teams, including training, tools help and operational reporting;
Acting as a key accelerator to growth by helping teams operate smarter, faster and more effectively.
You should have:
Undergraduate or graduate education in business, stats, economics or a relevant discipline;
4+ years experience as a sales operations leader, preferably in a high-growth technology or SaaS environment;
Extensive experience with Business Intelligence tools, such as Looker
Extensive experience with Salesforce.com and other inside sales technologies and productivity tools;
Deep understanding of leading and developing Sales Ops team models and functions, including salesforce management & performance, analytics, forecasting, incentives and attainment planning;
Strong leader with a natural eye for spotting and developing talent;
Deeply data-driven, naturally curious, and passionate about building data-driven organizations;
Ability to negotiate priorities and set expectations with senior-level stakeholders;
A deep analytical thinker and problem solver;
Strong focus on strategic thinking and analytical problem solving;
Meticulously organized and task-driven;
Strong interpersonal skills, excellent written and verbal communicator;
Self-motivated, independent, and deadline-oriented.
About Clio
At Clio, we're more than just a tech company. We're transforming the practice of law in a permanent and meaningful way that's bettering the lives of legal professionals while increasing access to justice for all. We are high achievers who are setting new standards for what it means to be a tech company. In the past three years, we've launched a new interface and experience of our software, acquired our first company, launched a second product, secured the largest Series D in Canadian history at the time, and launched a $1 million dollar relief fund to help legal professionals navigate the challenges of COVID-19 (just to name a few).

We are dedicated to creating diverse teams and inclusive workplaces. We know that different perspectives, skills, backgrounds, and experiences result in higher-performing teams and innovation. We believe you do your best work when you can show up as your authentic self—and that's a key part of our culture. At Clio, you have the chance to not only do the best work of your career but work that is putting Canada on the global stage. We know our technology changes lives and we're committed to making an impact. If that's something that speaks to you—you belong here, too. Join us.

Learn more about our culture and benefits at clio.com/careers
